{"lemma":"مَفْرَجُ","slug":"مَفْرَجُ","root":"ف.ر.ج","root_slug":"ف-ر-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ر-ج","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33390","n33391","n33392","n33393"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33390","headword_ar":"مَفْرَجٌ","root":"frj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furojapN","text_ar":"فُرْجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". [Hence]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maforaju Algami","text_ar":"مَفْرَجُ الغَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The place of opening of the mouth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$jr","text_ar":"شجر"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafaAriju","text_ar":"مَفَارِجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is its pl.; and] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Places of exit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"egress."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n33391","headword_ar":"مُفْرَجٌ","root":"frj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in the saying, in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA","text_ar":"لَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yutoraku fiY AlA_solaAmi muforajN","text_ar":"يُتْرَكُ فِى الاـسْلَامِ مُفْرَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [meaning that he who is thus termed shall not be left unbefriended among the Muslims,] is variously explained: As used to say that it is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and disapproved of the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mfrj","text_ar":"مفرج"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j","text_ar":"ج"},{"kind":"text","text":": A'Obeyd says, I heard Mohammad Ibn-El-Hasan say, it is related with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":"and with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j","text_ar":"ج"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and he who says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mfrj","text_ar":"مفرج"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j","text_ar":"ج"},{"kind":"text","text":", means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A slain person found in a desert tract, not by a town or village,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which signification is mentioned in the K,] the fine for whose blood is to be paid from the government-treasury: AO says that it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who becomes a Muslim and has no alliance of friendship with any one"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among the Muslims"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; wherefore, if he commits a crime, [such as maiming another, &c.,] the governmenttreasury must make amends for it, because he has no relations or others bound to aid him by paying a bloodwit [or the like]: (S, O: and the like is also said in the Mgh and in the K:) or, accord. to Jábir El-Joafee, it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man who is among a people to whom he does not belong;"},{"kind":"text","text":"wherefore they are bound to pay for him a bloodwit [or the like]: (O, TA:) or it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who has no kinsfolk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near relations:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so accord. to IAar: (Mgh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who has no offspring:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who has no wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it is also said to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one burdened by the obligation to pay a bloodwit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a ransom,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a debt that must be discharged:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [in like manner] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maforuwjN","text_ar":"مَفْرُوجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who is burdened with a debt:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but it is correctly with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[unpointed]; (TA;) [i. e.] such is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muforaHo","text_ar":"مُفْرَحْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":": (As, Mgh:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muforajN","text_ar":"مُفْرَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one burdened by his family,"},{"kind":"text","text":"although he be not in debt. (Az, TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muforaHN","text_ar":"مُفْرَحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.].)"}],"source_refs":["O","TA","Mgh","As"]},{"entry_id":"n33392","headword_ar":"مُفْرِجٌ","root":"frj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose shooting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"casting, has become altered"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the worse"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having been good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, O, * K.)       -A2-  And thus, without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", A hen"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having chickens."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n33393","headword_ar":"مُفَرَّجٌ","root":"frj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A camel (O)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose elbow is distant from his armpit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide in step:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) or, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", a she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose elbows are far from her chest, and whose armpits are"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"therefore"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 783.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A comb."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["O","K"]}]}}